<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Clone on an FPGA]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5706&amp;p=52062#p52062"><![CDATA[
Can't speak for others but I don't have one. My goal is to interface with original hardware and do so with as few gates as possible. So far I have most of a low-level PPU, composite video generator and a CPU without the PLA/instruction decoder. I haven't worked on it in nearly a year (too frustrating on a netbook) so there won't be any progress from me for a while. I understand some guys besides Kevtris do have games playable though.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Wed Nov 04, 2009 12:08 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
